A collection of colors

Author

Thomas Camminady

Published

July 6, 2023

1 Getting started

This is a collection of colors, an homage to the dicopal.js project. This website allows you to quickly browse a variety of color palettes and just copy their hex codes.

1.1 dicopal.js

dicopal.js deserves all credit for this work. I have only taken the palettes that they have collected and put them up on this page together with the hex codes. dicopal.js is using the Apache-2.0 license.

1.2 Stop talking, I want colors

You’ll find all palettes below in order sequential, diverging, qualitative. If you want to browse by source or type, use the table of contents.

Code 
from dicopal.create_page import create_page_by_type

path = "dicopal.js/src/palettes_apdocc.json"
create_page_by_type("sequential", path)
create_page_by_type("diverging", path)
create_page_by_type("qualitative", path)

1.530 How to use?

Either go to dicopal.js to use these palettes or copy the provided hex codes and hard-code them in your application.

I just wanted to have a collection of useful and beautiful colormaps from which I can copy the corresponding hex values when needed.
